  "riddle": "1. Seek the naval fleet that set sail prominently within the waters of China — in what year did it embark on its mission?\n\n2. Identify the ship whose name translates to \"light,\" and which carried traders before foreign vessels were common in Southeast Asia. In which century did this shift occur?\n\n3. What is the altitude where this vessel's presence is anchored, measured in meters above sea level?\n\n4. In a radius surrounding this ship's location, how many hospitals tend to the needs of the neighboring community?\n\n5. To proceed, add the altitude determined in clue 3 to the total count of hospitals from clue 4 — what number do you reach?\n\n6. Turn your attention to the celebrated French vessel that shares its name with a navigator's tool — how many meters long is this famous ship?\n\n7. From the pages of naval history, discover the elevation where Japan’s latest addition to their maritime pride stands. What is that measurement in meters?\n\n8. Extract the digital root of the value you retrieved in clue 7 — iterate the sum of its digits until a single digit remains. What number do you find?\n\n9. Finally, let's compute the essence of naval engagement: find the digital root of (clue 3 + clue 5 + clue 6 + clue 7). What is your single-digit answer?",
